gomodel:SYNGO_1948  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: NOS-I antibody: Zymed (South San Francisco, CA) (Table 1). Is characterized in this paper (no shown).\n\n21/11/2017 Pim\nFig.3: Authors note: \"Although the limited resolution of light microscopy prevents definite conclusions, these data are consistent with the hypothesis that sGC concentrates in axon terminals, whereas NOS-I concentrates in postsynaptic densities.\"\nFig.6: \"Quantitative EM of randomly selected asymmetric synapses in the stratum radiatum confirmed that gold particles coding for NOS-I were predominantly postsynaptic, concentrating just cytoplasmic to the postsynaptic membrane, whereas particles coding for sGCβ were predominantly presynaptic, concentrating ~15-25 nm cytoplasmic to the presynaptic membrane (Fig. 6 C).\". Experimental description: Mixed species are used: \"All procedures related to the care and treatment of animals were in accordance with institutional and National Institutes of Health guidelines. Ten male Sprague Dawley rats (200-350 gm; Charles River, Raleigh, NC) and eight male mice..\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1948" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

